CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper May 25, 1957, pg. A16, reads: "Victory Charity Club Contestants - When June 2 rolls around and the Victory Charily Club gives its annual tea, one of the two contestants for 'Miss Victory Charity Club' will wear the crown. The two fine women running for this honor are Mrs. Mozella Moore, second from right, and Mrs. Margaret Washington, far right. At the left is Mrs. Ruth Boyd Brooks, program chairman, and next to her is Mrs. William A. Brooks, general chairman. Viola Sams is president. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Members of Victory Charity Club, from left: Ruth Boyd Brooks, Mrs. William A. Brooks, Mozella Moore, and Margaret Washington posed in interior
